# Bat configuration file
# See `bat --help` for all available options
# This file contains command-line arguments, one per line

# Use a specific theme aligned with chussenot zsh theme
# TwoDark provides a dark theme that works well with cyan/green/yellow/red color scheme
# Available themes: 1337, Coldark-Cold, Coldark-Dark, DarkNeon, Dracula, GitHub, Monokai Extended, OneHalfDark, OneHalfLight, Solarized (dark), Solarized (light), TwoDark
--theme="TwoDark"

# Show line numbers, changes, and header
--style="numbers,changes,header"

# Use italic text
--italic-text="always"

# Show non-printable characters
# --show-all

# Use a specific pager
# --pager="less -R"

# Always show the header
--decorations="always"

# Color: let bat auto-detect (TTY → colored, pipe/redirect → plain)
# Forcing --color=always leaks ANSI escapes into pipes and redirected output.

# Wrap long lines
# --wrap="auto"
